{"lemma":"حامِلِي","slug":"حامِلِي","root":"ح.م.ل","root_slug":"ح-م-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-م-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حامِل","root":"حمل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9186"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%90%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pregnant","examples":[{"text":"لَوْ بَانَ بِٱلْكَرَمِ ٱلْجَنِينُ بَيَانَهُ / لَدَرَتْ بِهِ ذَكَرٌ أَمُ ٱنْثَى ٱلْحَامِلُ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of حَمَلَ (ḥamala, “to carry”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9186","headword_ar":"حَامِلٌ","root":"Hml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bearing, carrying, taking up and carrying, conveying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carrying off"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] act. part. n. of 1 having for its object what is borne on the back [&c.]: (Msb:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamalapN","text_ar":"حَمَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmilaAtN","text_ar":"حَامِلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamalapu AlEaro$i","text_ar":"حَمَلَةُ العَرْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bearers of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er$","text_ar":"عرش"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"empyrean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"held by the vulgar to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the throne of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@loHaAmilaAti wiqorFA","text_ar":"فَا@لْحَامِلَاتِ وِقْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur li. 2, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the bearers of a load,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy load:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a woman, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pregnant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmilapN","text_ar":"حَامِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) the former as being an epithet exclusively applied to a female: the latter as conformable to its verb, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamalato","text_ar":"حَمَلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) or as being used in a tropical [or doubly tropical] manner, meaning pregnant in past time or in future time; (Msb;) or as a possessive epithet [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a burden in the womb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [see an ex. of the latter in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mxS","text_ar":"مخص"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to the Koofees, the former, not being applied to a male, has no need of the sign of the fem. gender: but the Basrees say that this [rule] does not uniformly obtain; for the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN A^ay~imN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ اَيِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN A^ay~imN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ اَيِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN EaAnisN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ عَانِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN EaAnisN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ عَانِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that, correctly speaking,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmilN","text_ar":"حَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iDN","text_ar":"حَايِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like are epithets masc. in form applied to females, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboEapN","text_ar":"رَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwiyapN","text_ar":"رَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xujaA^apN","text_ar":"خُجَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are epithets fem. in form applied to males. (S.) It is also applied to a she-camel [and app. to any female] in the same sense. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Applied to trees ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarN","text_ar":"شَجَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bearing fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiylN","text_ar":"حَمِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  [Respecting this epithet, and the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmilu AlA^amaAnapi","text_ar":"حَامِلُ الاَمَانَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHotamilu","text_ar":"مُحْتَمِلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amaAnapi","text_ar":"الاَمَانَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAnapN","text_ar":"اَمَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one.] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hamalapu AlquraA=ni","text_ar":"حَمَلَةُ القُرَا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those who bear in their memory the Kur-án, knowing it by heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}